          "bodyHtml": "<p><strong>China</strong> has shipped 53 tonnes of tents to aid earthquake-hit <strong>Turkey</strong> on Sunday, state broadcaster CCTV said.</p> <p>The tents departed Shanghai on large cargo planes and are scheduled to arrive in Istanbul later on Sunday, the broadcaster added, Reuters reports.</p> <p>The first batch of supplies from China’s government, 40,000 blankets, arrived in Istanbul on Saturday, according to CCTV.</p> <p>It added that the country is planning to send medical equipment, including electrocardiogram machines, ultrasound diagnostic instruments, medical vehicles and hospital beds in the near future.</p> <p>A rescue team of 82 members dispatched by the Chinese government arrived in Turkey on Wednesday, CCTV reported.</p>",
