                "html": "<p><strong>Greece’s</strong> foreign minister Nikos Dendias arrived in <strong>Turkey</strong> on Sunday in a show of support, the ministry said, despite a longstanding rivalry between the two Nato countries.</p> \n<p>Dendias was met by his <strong>Turkish</strong> counterpart Mevlut Cavusoglu, according to footage on state-run ERT TV, before they boarded helicopters to visit the quake-hit regions, Agence France-Presse reports. </p> \n<p>His arrival marks the first visit by a European minister to Turkey since the earthquake.</p> \n<p>The two ministers are travelling to Antakya, where Greek rescuers are helping with search and rescue operations.</p> \n<p>The ministry said he will also visit members of the Greek Aid Mission in the country.</p> \n<p>So far, the Greek government has sent 80 tonnes of medical and first aid equipment.</p> \n<p>According to the ministry, the foreign minister will also discuss ways Greece can give further assistance to Turkey.</p>"
